{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/infoFileName","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/savedStatesDirectory"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Properties","title":"Type Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/delete(bundle:label:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/list(bundle:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/restore(bundle:label:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/save(bundle:label:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Methods","title":"Type Methods"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/snapshotmanager"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotInfo","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotError"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Snapshots","title":"Snapshots"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"metadata":{"title":"SnapshotManager","symbolKind":"enum","roleHeading":"Enumeration","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}],"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit15SnapshotManagerO","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SnapshotManager"},{"type":"text","text":" provides save, restore, list, and delete"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operations for VM snapshots. Each snapshot is a full copy of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the VM’s disk image ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"disk.img"},{"type":"text","text":"), auxiliary storage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"auxiliary.bin"},{"type":"text","text":"), and machine identifier ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"machine-identifier.bin"},{"type":"text","text":"),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stored in a named subdirectory under the bundle’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SavedStates\/"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directory."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"How-Snapshots-Work","text":"How Snapshots Work","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike VZ state save (which captures in-memory VM state and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"requires the VM to be running in the same process),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"disk-level snapshots copy the on-disk artifacts. This means:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The VM ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"must be stopped"}]},{"text":" before saving or restoring.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Snapshots work across processes and reboots.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Restoring replaces the current disk and auxiliary storage","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with the snapshot copies.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"APFS-Copy-on-Write","text":"APFS Copy-on-Write","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On APFS volumes, both save and restore use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FileManager.copyItem"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which the system maps to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"clonefile(2)"},{"type":"text","text":". This produces a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"copy-on-write clone instead of a byte-for-byte copy, making"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"snapshot creation and restoration near-instantaneous regardless"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of disk image size. Only blocks that diverge after the clone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consume additional storage."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Snapshot-Directory-Layout","text":"Snapshot Directory Layout","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":null,"code":["my-vm.vm\/","├── disk.img","├── auxiliary.bin","├── machine-identifier.bin","├── ...","└── SavedStates\/","    ├── clean-install\/","    │   ├── disk.img","    │   ├── auxiliary.bin","    │   ├── machine-identifier.bin","    │   └── snapshot-info.json","    └── before-xcode\/","        ├── disk.img","        ├── auxiliary.bin","        ├── machine-identifier.bin","        └── snapshot-info.json"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Example","text":"Example","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","","\/\/ Save a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.save(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")","","\/\/ List snapshots","let snapshots = try SnapshotManager.list(bundle: bundle)","for snap in snapshots {","    print(\"\\(snap.label): \\(snap.sizeInBytes) bytes\")","}","","\/\/ Restore a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.restore(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")","","\/\/ Delete a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.delete(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")"],"type":"codeListing"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Manages disk-level snapshots for virtual machine bundles.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/SnapshotManager/infoFileName":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/infoFileName","title":"infoFileName","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"infoFileName","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/snapshotmanager\/infofilename","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The file name for snapshot metadata inside each snapshot directory."}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/SnapshotInfo":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotInfo","title":"SnapshotInfo","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SnapshotInfo","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SnapshotInfo","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/snapshotinfo","abstract":[{"text":"Metadata about a saved VM snapshot.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/SnapshotManager/list(bundle:)":{"title":"list(bundle:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/list(bundle:)","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"list"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"bundle"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15SpooktacularKit20VirtualMachineBundleV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Vi